rules: Rule1: Either the farm cooperative produces corn or the corn is edible.
Rule2: Whenever the corn is distributed to market, it is packaged.
Rule3: Either the corn is distributed to market or, if it is not the case that treated with pesticide implies edible, then the corn is quarantined.
Rule4: Whenever the corn is stored properly, then if it is packaged, it is available retail.
Rule5: Either the corn is stored properly or it is temperature controlled.
Rule6: If the corn is temperature controlled, then whenever it is packaged, it is available retail.
Rule7: Provided that the corn is sent to factory, then either it is processed into food or it is edible.
Rule8: Either the corn is sent to factory or it is received by processor.
Rule9: Whenever the corn is on schedule, then if it is received by processor, either it is processed into food or it is edible.
Rule10: If transport is arranged for the corn, then it is on schedule.
Rule11: Provided that the farm cooperative requires transport, then it does not produce corn.
Rule12: Either the farm cooperative requires transport or it uses refrigeration.
Rule13: Under the condition that the corn undergoes international shipping, it has cleared customs.

Rule14: Either the corn is domestic only or, if it has export documentation, then whenever it is not the case that export approved implies the farm cooperative does not produce corn, the corn undergoes international shipping.
Rule15: If the corn is safe for consumption, then it is edible.
Rule16: Whenever the corn is tested in laboratory, then if it is treated with pesticide, it is safe for consumption.
Rule17: If the corn undergoes quality assurance, then it is tested in laboratory.
Rule18: Provided that cooking is required for the corn, then it is processed into food.
Rule19: Either cooking is required for the corn or it is ready to eat.
Rule20: Under the condition that the corn is pre-cooked, it is edible.
Rule21: Whenever the corn passes inspection, it is certified organic.
Rule22: Under the condition that the corn passes inspection, then it does not meet standard.
Rule23: Provided that the corn is certified organic, it meets standard.
Rule24: If the corn has pest infestation, then it is edible.
Rule25: Either the corn has pest infestation or it is treated with pesticide.
Rule26: Whenever it is not the case that export restricted implies the corn is not domestic only, then the corn has banned export.
Rule27: Provided that it is not the case that uses refrigeration implies the farm cooperative does not produce corn, then the corn passes inspection.

Rule28: Whenever it is not the case that food safety regulation implies that not being raw product or ready to eat implies pre-cooked leads to processed product, then the corn has compliance exception.
Rule29: Provided that it is not the case that not having export restricted implies not domestic only leads to not having banned export, then the corn has special permit.
Rule30: If it is not the case that not having export restricted implies not domestic only leads to not having banned export, then the corn does not have special permit.
facts: Fact1: Transport is arranged for the corn.
Fact2: Export is approved for the corn.
Fact3: The corn has export documentation.
Fact4: The corn is export restricted.
Fact5: The corn undergoes quality assurance.
Fact6: The corn is subject to food safety regulation.
Fact7: The corn is not available retail.
Fact8: The corn is not processed into food.
Fact9: The corn has not cleared customs.
Fact10: The corn is not a raw product.
Fact11: The corn is not a processed product.
Fact12: The corn does not have compliance exception.
Fact13: The corn is not quarantined.
